detaileddescription.para: This method checks whether or not the BCH code in d_rcv_tmcc_data is correct.
Prints the decoded TMCC in d_rcv_tmcc_data in a somewhat nice and human-readable format.

briefdescription.para: The method decodes the TMCC carriers of a given symbol, thus appending a new bit to those received so far. If 203 were received since the last complete tmcc, we check whether the sync word if present at the beginning, and if it passes the BCH parity code.

detaileddescription.para: Our present implementation simply performs the differential demodulation (TMCC is transmitted in DBPSK) for every carrier, and then performs a majority vote between all carriers to verify which bit was sent.
Sets several parameters used throughout the rest of the methods
it constructs the d_data_carriers list, which contains the list of carriers that have actual DTV data.
